ation/WWDCNotes/WWDC24-10074-Get-started-with-Dynamic-Type":{"role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc24-10074-get-started-with-dynamic-type","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC24-10074-Get-started-with-Dynamic-Type","kind":"article","title":"Get started with Dynamic Type","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Dynamic Type lets people choose their preferred text size across the system and all of their apps. To help you get started supporting Dynamic Type, we’ll cover the fundamentals: How it works, how to find issues with scaling text in your app, and how to take practical steps using SwiftUI and UIKit to create a great Dynamic Type experience. We’ll also show how you can best use the Large Content Viewer to make navigation controls accessible to everyone.","type":"text"}]},"WWDC25-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","type":"image"}}}